<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug B</strong> — <code>interact</code> should run only when there is a <strong>gap</strong> ahead. This flips a lever on every step.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">while True:
    agent.interact(...)
    agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Why was it wrong? Why does your fix work?</strong></p>
<p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p><p class="ruled">&nbsp;</p>

<p><strong>Bug C</strong> — A sticky piston holds the bridge <strong>only while the lever is ON</strong>. The second <code>interact</code> turns it OFF and the bridge vanishes, so cross first.</p>
<pre><code class="language-python">agent.interact(...)
agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
agent.interact(...)
agent.move(FORWARD, 1)
</code></pre>
<p><strong>Fixed code:</strong></p>
